    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">DS10 -- SRM Boot, Commands &amp; SuperIO Controller</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The DS10 firmware reference. SRM boot and the <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> command set are covered operationally in the Quick Start and Operating EmulatR chapters; this appendix records the DS10-specific SuperIO analysis -- the part of the platform that is unique reference material rather than general operation.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">SRM boot and commands (pointers)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Reaching the <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> prompt and the boot sequence are described under Quick Start; the console command catalogue (<text styleclass="Code Example">show config</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">show device</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">boot</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">set</text>, and the rest) is under Operating EmulatR. The notes below assume that context and focus on the SuperIO programming the firmware performs during initialization.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">SuperIO controller -- word-fold (confirmed)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The Cypress CY82C693 SuperIO is configured through 16-bit writes that fold an index byte and a data byte into one word: the low byte is the index, the high byte is the data. This byte order is locked and confirmed -- the 0x22 / 0x23 power-control writes carry their Table 61 default data bytes, and the configuration splits cleanly into <text styleclass="Code Example">port 0x3F0</text> (index) / <text styleclass="Code Example">port 0x3F1</text> (data):</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">SIO-TRACE W port=0x3F0 val=0x60 [cfg] index 0x60</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">SIO-TRACE W port=0x3F1 val=0x03 [cfg] data 0x03 (FDD base high)</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">SIO-TRACE W port=0x3F0 val=0x70 [cfg] index 0x70</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">SIO-TRACE W port=0x3F1 val=0x06 [cfg] data 0x06 (IRQ6)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Logical device map</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The firmware programs every logical device in turn (selecting each via index 0x07 = LDN, then base / IRQ / DMA / activate). The resulting assignment matches <text styleclass="Code Example">show config</text> exactly:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="5" colcount="5" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">LDN</text></para>
        </td>
