        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Serial (COM1)</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">0x03F8</text></para>
        </td>
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Normal">IRQ4</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">5</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Serial (COM2)</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">0x02F8</text></para>
        </td>
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Normal">IRQ3</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The configuration is grounded end to end in the HRM trace: 93 SIO-TRACE config lines, every one splitting cleanly into index / data, with the FDD logical device landing at 0x03F0 / IRQ6 / DMA2. The SuperIO is properly modeled and the byte-fold is confirmed beyond doubt.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
